\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. A. santolinoides} Lag., {\i Gen. Sp. Nov.} 30 (1816). Tomentose, more or less glabrescent dwarf shrub. Stems up to 40(-60) cm, ascending, much-branched above. Leaves up to 1·5 × 0·3 cm, terete, sessile, patent, rarely glabrous, 1- to 2-pinnatifid, the lobes suborbicular, spinulose. Corymbs with 4-9 capitula; peduncles 3-15 mm. Involucre 4·5-6 mm in diameter; bracts 2-3 mm ovate, obtuse, usually tomentose, with a scarious margin. Ligules 1-2 mm, orbicular or wider than long, yellow.{\i  Waste ground. S.E. Spain}. Hs. ({\i N. Africa}.)
\par

